<topic id='attribute_cancer_care_spell_delay_reason_comment.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>Attribute: CANCER CARE SPELL DELAY REASON COMMENT - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>

  <p>
A comment why a 
    <xref outputclass="attribute"
            keyref="attribute_cancer_care_spell_delay_reason">CANCER CARE SPELL DELAY REASON</xref>
 was experienced.  </p>
  <p>This can be recorded for:</p>
  <ul>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>
each breach of existing service standards (introduced by the 
                <xref href="https://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/+/http://www.dh.gov.uk/en/Publicationsandstatistics/Publications/PublicationsPolicyAndGuidance/DH_4009609"
                     scope="external"
                     format="html">'NHS Cancer Plan (2000)'</xref>
)        </p>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>
the extended service standards (as specified within the 
                <xref href="https://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/+/http://www.dh.gov.uk/en/Healthcare/Cancer/DH_091120"
                     scope="external"
                     format="html">'Cancer Reform Strategy (2007)'</xref>
) and        </p>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>
the 28 Day Faster Diagnosis Standard (introduced by the independent Cancer Taskforce 
                <xref href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/cancer/strategy/"
                     scope="external"
                     format="html">'Achieving World-Class Cancer Outcomes'</xref>
)        </p>
         </div>
      </li>
  </ul>
  <p>after any patient pauses have been taken into account.</p>
  <p>
The standards for which a 
    <xref outputclass="attribute"
            keyref="attribute_cancer_care_spell_delay_reason_comment">CANCER CARE SPELL DELAY REASON COMMENT</xref>
 can be given are:  </p>
  <ul>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>
maximum two week wait** for an urgent 
                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_general_practitioner">GENERAL PRACTITIONER</xref>
 referral for suspected cancer to 
                <xref outputclass="element" keyref="element_date_first_seen">DATE FIRST SEEN</xref>
 for all suspected cancers        </p>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>
maximum 28 day wait for an urgent 
                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_general_practitioner">GENERAL PRACTITIONER</xref>
 referral or referral for suspected cancer from an NHS Cancer 
                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                     keyref="business_definition_screening_programme">Screening Programme</xref>
 for suspected cancer, where the 
                <xref outputclass="attribute"
                     keyref="attribute_cancer_faster_diagnosis_pathway_end_reason">CANCER FASTER DIAGNOSIS PATHWAY END REASON</xref>
 is National Code 
                <i>'Diagnosis of cancer'</i>
 or 
                <i>'Ruling out of cancer'</i>
            </p>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>
maximum 28 day wait for an urgent 
                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_general_practitioner">GENERAL PRACTITIONER</xref>
 referral, referral for breast symptoms (where cancer is not initially suspected) or referral for suspected cancer from an NHS Cancer 
                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                     keyref="business_definition_screening_programme">Screening Programme</xref>
 for suspected cancer, where the 
                <xref outputclass="attribute"
                     keyref="attribute_cancer_faster_diagnosis_pathway_end_reason">CANCER FASTER DIAGNOSIS PATHWAY END REASON</xref>
 is National Code 
                <i>'Diagnosis of cancer'</i>
 or 
                <i>'Ruling out of cancer'</i>
            </p>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>
maximum one month** wait from urgent 
                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_general_practitioner">GENERAL PRACTITIONER</xref>
 referral for suspected cancer to 
                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                     keyref="business_definition_first_definitive_treatment">First Definitive Treatment</xref>
 for testicular cancer, acute leukaemia and children's cancer (under 16 years of age at date of 
                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                     keyref="business_definition_first_definitive_treatment">First Definitive Treatment</xref>
)*        </p>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>
maximum two month wait** from urgent 
                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_general_practitioner">GENERAL PRACTITIONER</xref>
 referral for suspected cancer to 
                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                     keyref="business_definition_first_definitive_treatment">First Definitive Treatment</xref>
 for all cancers        </p>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>
maximum one month wait** from 
                <xref outputclass="element"
                     keyref="element_cancer_treatment_period_start_date">CANCER TREATMENT PERIOD START DATE</xref>
 (
                <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_decision_to_treat_date">DECISION TO TREAT DATE</xref>
) to 
                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                     keyref="business_definition_first_definitive_treatment">First Definitive Treatment</xref>
 for all cancers        </p>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>
maximum 31-day wait from 
                <xref outputclass="element"
                     keyref="element_cancer_treatment_period_start_date">CANCER TREATMENT PERIOD START DATE</xref>
 (
                <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_decision_to_treat_date">DECISION TO TREAT DATE</xref>
 or 
                <xref outputclass="element"
                     keyref="element_earliest_clinically_appropriate_date">EARLIEST CLINICALLY APPROPRIATE DATE</xref>
) to the start of second or subsequent treatment for all cancers, where the 
                <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_cancer_treatment_modality">CANCER TREATMENT MODALITY</xref>
 is National Code 
                <i>'</i>
               <i>
                  <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_chemoradiotherapy">Chemoradiotherapy</xref>
               </i>
               <i>'</i>
, 
                <i>
'
                  <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_teletherapy">Teletherapy</xref>
 (Beam Radiation excluding 
                  <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_proton_therapy">Proton Therapy</xref>
)'          </i>
,
                <i>
'
                  <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_brachytherapy">Brachytherapy</xref>
'          </i>
 or 
                <i>
'
                  <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_proton_therapy">Proton Therapy</xref>
'          </i>
            </p>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>
maximum 31-day wait from 
                <xref outputclass="element"
                     keyref="element_cancer_treatment_period_start_date">CANCER TREATMENT PERIOD START DATE</xref>
 (
                <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_decision_to_treat_date">DECISION TO TREAT DATE</xref>
 or 
                <xref outputclass="element"
                     keyref="element_earliest_clinically_appropriate_date">EARLIEST CLINICALLY APPROPRIATE DATE</xref>
) to start of second or subsequent treatment for all cancers where the 
                <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_cancer_treatment_modality">CANCER TREATMENT MODALITY</xref>
 is National Code 
                <i>'Surgery'</i>
            </p>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>
maximum 31-day wait from 
                <xref outputclass="element"
                     keyref="element_cancer_treatment_period_start_date">CANCER TREATMENT PERIOD START DATE</xref>
 (
                <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_decision_to_treat_date">DECISION TO TREAT DATE</xref>
 or 
                <xref outputclass="element"
                     keyref="element_earliest_clinically_appropriate_date">EARLIEST CLINICALLY APPROPRIATE DATE</xref>
) to start of second or subsequent treatment for all cancers where the 
                <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_cancer_treatment_modality">CANCER TREATMENT MODALITY</xref>
 is National Code 
                <i>
'
                  <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_anti-cancer_drug_regimen">Anti-Cancer Drug Regimen</xref>
               </i>
               <i>
(
                  <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_cytotoxic_chemotherapy">Cytotoxic Chemotherapy</xref>
)'          </i>
, 
                <i>
'
                  <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_anti-cancer_drug_regimen">Anti-Cancer Drug Regimen</xref>
               </i>
               <i>
(
                  <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_hormone_therapy">Hormone Therapy</xref>
)'          </i>
, 
                <i>
'
                  <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_anti-cancer_drug_regimen">Anti-Cancer Drug Regimen</xref>
 (
                  <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_immunotherapy">Immunotherapy</xref>
)'          </i>
 or 
                <i>
'
                  <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_anti-cancer_drug_regimen">Anti-Cancer Drug Regimen</xref>
               </i>
               <i>(other)'</i>
            </p>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>
maximum 31-day wait from 
                <xref outputclass="element"
                     keyref="element_cancer_treatment_period_start_date">CANCER TREATMENT PERIOD START DATE</xref>
 (
                <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_decision_to_treat_date">DECISION TO TREAT DATE</xref>
 or 
                <xref outputclass="element"
                     keyref="element_earliest_clinically_appropriate_date">EARLIEST CLINICALLY APPROPRIATE DATE</xref>
) to start of second or subsequent treatment for all cancers where the 
                <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_cancer_treatment_modality">CANCER TREATMENT MODALITY</xref>
 is other than National Code 
                <i>'Surgery'</i>
, 
                <i>
'
                  <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_anti-cancer_drug_regimen">Anti-Cancer Drug Regimen</xref>
'          </i>
, 
                <i>
'
                  <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_chemoradiotherapy">Chemoradiotherapy</xref>
'          </i>
, 
                <i>
'
                  <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_teletherapy">Teletherapy</xref>
 (Beam Radiation excluding 
                  <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_proton_therapy">Proton Therapy</xref>
)'          </i>
,
                <i>
'
                  <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_brachytherapy">Brachytherapy</xref>
'          </i>
 or 
                <i>
'
                  <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_proton_therapy">Proton Therapy</xref>
'          </i>
            </p>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>
maximum 62-day wait from referral for suspected cancer from an NHS Cancer 
                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                     keyref="business_definition_screening_programme">Screening Programme</xref>
 to 
                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                     keyref="business_definition_first_definitive_treatment">First Definitive Treatment</xref>
 for breast, bowel and cervical cancers*        </p>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>
maximum 62-day wait from a decision to upgrade the priority of a 
                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENT</xref>
 by a 
                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_consultant">CONSULTANT</xref>
 (or authorised member of a 
                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_consultant">CONSULTANT</xref>
 team) to 
                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                     keyref="business_definition_first_definitive_treatment">First Definitive Treatment</xref>
         </p>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>
maximum two week wait** for an urgent referral for breast symptoms (where cancer is not initially suspected) to 
                <xref outputclass="element" keyref="element_date_first_seen">DATE FIRST SEEN</xref>
.        </p>
         </div>
      </li>
  </ul>
  <p>Notes:</p>
  <p>
* Breast, bowel, cervical and testicular cancer and acute leukaemia are defined by 
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_information/clinical_coding/international_classification_of_diseases_(icd).asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">International_Classification_of_Diseases_(ICD)</xref>
 diagnosis codes. The full list of diagnosis codes can be found on the 
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
            keyref="business_definition_nhs_digital">NHS Digital</xref>
 website at: 
    <xref href="https://digital.nhs.uk/cancer-waiting-times"
            scope="external"
            format="html">Cancer Waiting Times</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
** For the performance management and the requirement to record a 
    <xref outputclass="attribute"
            keyref="attribute_cancer_care_spell_delay_reason_comment">CANCER CARE SPELL DELAY REASON COMMENT</xref>
 for the above service standards, the following standardised time periods have been identified:  </p>
  <simpletable outputclass="simpletable table table-striped table-sm">
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <b>Time Period</b>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <b>Number of Calendar Days</b>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>Two Weeks</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>14</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>Twenty Eight Days</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>28</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>One Month</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>31</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
      <strow>
         <stentry>
            <p>Two Months</p>
         </stentry>
         <stentry>
            <p>62</p>
         </stentry>
      </strow>
  </simpletable>

</body>
